summary: New S32K5 microcontroller family advances zonal SDV architectures and extends the NXP CoreRide platform NXP today unveiled its new S32K5 family of automotive microcontrollers (MCU), the automotive industry's first 16nm FinFET MCU with embedded magnetic RAM (MRAM).
